The functional surface groups were investigated using FTIR spectroscopy (Fig. 2
                     ). The peaks shown at 3424, 3236, 2923/2850, 1656, 1412, 1320 and 1116 and 1096 cm−1 are assigned to –OH, N-H, C-H, C=O (carbonyl), COO- (carboxylate), C-OH (hydroxyl) and C-O-C (epoxide) [16,17] groups, respectively. The presence of such functional groups implies that the synthesized CDs have excellent water-soluble colloidal dispersion [18]. It was also found that these dots are negatively charged with ξ-potential = 32 mV in 10 mM PBS, the negative charge could be ascribed to the existence of oxygenated functional groups [19–21]
                     .
